    <li><span class="label">[S.3]</span> Moser, Max, et al. (2025). <strong>Supporting patients receiving long-term psychodynamic psychotherapy: A semi-structured interview study into the lived experiences of providers and carers</strong>. Manuscript under review at <em>Psychotherapy</em>.</li>

    <li><span class="label">[S.2]</span> Moser, Max, et al. (2025). <strong>Long-term psychodynamic psychotherapy for depression and complex depression: A systematic review and meta-analysis of randomized controlled trials</strong>. Manuscript submitted for publication in <em>World Psychiatry</em>.</li>

    <li><span class="label">[S.1]</span> Moser, Max, et al. (2025). <strong>Patient experiences of long-term psychodynamic psychotherapy for mood and personality disorders: A systematic review and meta-aggregation of qualitative studies</strong>. Manuscript accepted for publication in <em>Journal of Counseling Psychology</em>.</li>

    <li><span class="label">[J.3]</span> Luyten, P., Moser, M., & Fonagy, P. (2025). <strong><a href="https://doi.org/10.1177/00048674251321761">Letter to the editor: Serious concerns about ‘Concerns over the process and outcomes of the review by the Royal Australian and New Zealand College of Psychiatrists into long-term psychodynamic psychotherapy’</a></strong>. <em>Australian & New Zealand Journal of Psychiatry</em>, 59(7), 651–652.</li>

    <li><span class="label">[J.2]</span> Moser, Max, Barrett, A., Ozols, I., et al. (2024). <strong>Mood disorders psychodynamic psychotherapy evidence review: A mixed-methods review of current evidence and interview study of long-term psychodynamic psychotherapy as a treatment for mood disorders</strong>. Report to the Royal Australian and New Zealand College of Psychiatrists. London: Anna Freud Centre.</li>

    <li><span class="label">[P.1]</span> Moser, Max. (2024). <strong><a href="https://www.fastcompany.com/91237453/why-gaining-power-makes-us-out-of-touch-with-the-people-we-lead">Why gaining power makes us out of touch with the people we lead</a></strong>. <em>Fast Company</em>.</li>

    <li><span class="label">[J.1]</span> Luyten, Patrick, Campbell, Chloe, Moser, Max, Fonagy, Peter (2024). <strong><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cpr.2024.102380">The role of mentalizing in psychological interventions in adults: Systematic review and recommendations for future research</a></strong>. <em>Clinical Psychology Review</em>, Vol. 108, March 2024, pp. 102380.</li>
